 ACTOR Kenneth Nkosi has been arrested. He is being held in the cells at Central Joburg Police
station. Kenneth was arrested for the incident that happened on
Friday night. He allegedly assaulted a woman at BlackAnt Lounge in
Newtown, Joburg, during his birthday celebration. The woman spoke to Daily Sun and said that she opened
a case against the actor and wanted him arrested. Today, the actor handed himself over to the police at Joburg
central. News of the incident first broke on Twitter after the
victim’s friend Puly voiced her anger, posting a photo of Kenneth with a string
of angry messages. She posted a video of a drunk-looking Kenneth lighting a
cigarette while Mosidi begged him to return her phone. She wrote in the caption: “He busted her lip, followed her
to the bathroom, and beat her up some more.”  